text.section:
A person is guilty of failure to maintain a register of metals and objects containing metal when the person fails or refuses to:
Obtain the information required by KRS 433.890;
Keep the records required by KRS 433.890 for the period of time required in KRS 433.890;
Provide the required records to the police department or sheriff as required by KRS 433.890;
Provide access to a peace officer to records required to be kept pursuant to KRS 433.890; or
Dispose of the records required to be maintained pursuant to KRS 433.890 in a manner meeting the requirements of KRS 433.890.
